deck: Both he and his cousin, also named Wally after their great grandfather, were struck by lightning and infused with the Speed Force. This Wally is the new Kid Flash.
description:
Wally is the son of Danny West, nephew to Iris West Allen and Rudolph West, and cousin to the original Kid Flash, Wally West. The two Wallys have met once and share little in common rather than an aunt, and connection to the speed force. He is the newest host of the speed force and newest Kid Flash. Wally struggles to balance heroism with school and the lack of trust Barry shows him.

Powers

Speed Force Conduit: As a conduit of the Speed Force, KF's physiology is enhanced in many different ways.

  • Superhuman Speed, Reflexes, Agility, Stamina, and Durability
  • Protective Speed Force Aura
  • Speed Force Constructs
  • Lightning Generation/Projection
  • Steal Speed
  • Molecular/Kinetic Acceleration
  • Cyclone Creation

Other Media

Television

The Flash

Wally West appears in Season 2 of the series, portrayed by Keiynan Lonsdale. In a departure from the comics, this version of Wally is Iris West's younger brother, rather than her nephew. His future as a speedster is alluded to numerous times, with Wally initially engaging in illegal street racing to pay for his mother's medical bills, and again when he states that he one day wants to have a high speed profession like an astronaut or a fighter pilot.

He becomes a great admirator of the Flash and decides he wants to become someone worthy of having been saved, going as far as trying to help him fend off invading metahumans when Zoom lays siege to Central City; meanwhile, he also starts to grow closer to Barry Allen. Wally is infused with Barry's energy when Barry is warped into the Speed Force, but has yet to develop any powers. He realizes Barry and the Flash are one and the same when Zoom attacks them at a family reunion.

deck: Survivor of the Crossed epidemic who toured the country with her twin sister.
description:
Origin

Hating their stepfather, Ashlynne and her twin sister Ashley uploaded nude pictures of themselves on their stepfather's laptop for their mother could find them. Their mother called the cops, who, unbeknownst to her, were infected by the Crossed virus. Ashlynne and her sister got away in a car and went to their biological father.

On their search for a save haven, they met Leon, Steve and Gregory Costello. But one day, Ashley stepped into a bear trap and was unable to run away from the Crossed. She became one of them. Her sister Ashlynne tried to save her and succumbed to the Crossed as well.

Powers & Abilities

Ashlynne has an N.R.A. Junior Sharpshooter medal.
name: Ashlynne

deck: Former military intelligence, and survivor of the Crossed epidemic.
description:
Origin

Stevegot her first thrill of killing, when her father popped a brain vein in a play fight with her. Her ex-husband had a bad reaction to pain killers he needed to endure their sex plays. In the military intelligence, she saw the detainees being manhandled by the guards. Leaving the military, she got into personal security.

She killed her client and fed him to the Crossed as a distraction. She crossed America alone on her bike, until she met Gregory Costello. After a short bout of sex with Gregory, she accidently became pregnant. She gave birth to a son, after she had survived her teammates Gregory, Leon and the twin sisters Ashley and Ashlynne had all been infected by the Crossed virus.
name: Steve

deck: Survivor of the Crossed epidemic.
description:
Origin

Gregory Costello was living in Arcadia, Virginia, married with two kids, a girl and a boy. When the Crossed epidemic spread through the world, he was away from his family. His wife called him on the phone to tell him the neighbors were acting savagely. She was in panic. Gregory never went home. Instead, he stepped on his bike and crossed the country. On his journey, he met Steve, Leon and the twin sisters Ashley and Ashlynne.

Shot in his knee, Gregory was left behind by Steve. The twin sisters, who had become infected by the Crossed, infected Gregory as well. They later beheaded him.
name: Gregory Costello

deck: Leon lives with his family in the swamps, keeping the Crossed behind a prison wall.
description:
Origin

Leon lives with his father Clint behind prison walls with most of his family. He runs a meth lab, which sometimes distracts him from his duty to ward off the Crossed.

After his abusive father had locked him in a dump as punishment, Leon took revenge by mixing some of the Crossed blood in his meth products. Soon the camp was infected. He blew up the camp with some grenades and fled by boat. His father survived the blast and went on to hunt his son down.

On his travels, he met the twin sisters Ashley and Ashlynne. Later on, Steve and Gregory Costello joined the band, fighting together against the Crossed, one of which was his father Clint. Shortly after he killed his father, he himself was killed by one of the twin girls.
name: Leon

deck: A survivor of the Crossed epidemic and father of Leon.
description:
Origin

Trying to be a leader of the prison camp (in which survivors of the Crossed epidemic lived together), Clint sometimes had to enforce the rules. After his son Leon was negligent in his guard duty, which cost the life of Clint's favorite dog, Clint locked his son up on a dump tank as a punishment. Leon took revenge by mixing some of the Crossed blood in his meth products. Soon the camp was infected. He blew up the camp with some grenades and fled by boat. His father survived the blast and went on to hunt his son down. Soon, Clint came across some of his family members who had turned into the Crossed. For some reason, he joined them as one of the Crossed. As soon as he tried to come close to his son, Leon shot him dead.
name: Clint

deck: Bill Brane hired Jack Ryder (The Creeper) after he was fired from his TV Show.
description:
Origin

Bill Brane hired Jack Ryder (The Creeper) after he was fired from his TV Show. Mr. Ryder was fired for standing by his principles live on TV. It was this act that Mr. Brane admired. Mr. Ryder's first assignment was capturing Angel Deviln. It was this assignment that turned Mr. Ryder into the Creeper. It was after that, that Mr. Brane had Mr. Ryder guard the weather girl Vera Sweet. This was not an assignment that Mr. Ryder took seriously. He would often abandon Ms. Sweet to become the Creeper. Despite this, Mr. Ryder was able to keep his job by getting other assignments done. Like capturing Proteus whom impersonated both the Creeper and Mr. Brane.

Creation

Bill Brane was created by Steve Ditko. His first appearance is shared with Creeper in Showcase 73.

deck: Gerk Kreg is a mob boss and an enemy of the Creeper.

Origin

Gerk Kreg is a mob boss who hates the Creeper as much as the the police. He put out a hit on the Creeper. A hit that was never collected. That doesn't mean he didn't get his licks in however, Mr. Kreg even knocked him out once and could have killed him himself if he didn't wait to find out who the Creeper was under what he thought was a costume. Unfortunately, for Mr. Kreg his entire gang is rounded up by the police while trying to catch the Creeper.

Creation

Gerk Kreg was created by Steve Ditko and first appeared in Beware the Creeper 1. Gerk Kerg's name is a palindrome. That means his name is the same spelled backwards and forwards.
name: Gerk Kreg
